      "date": "2012-12-06 01:17:25.000000000",
      "message": "Patch Set 2: I would prefer that you didn't submit this\n\n(6 inline comments)\n\nMaybe I'm missing some understanding, but I thought the \"target\" code would control all of the things like thread start/stop, recovery, etc, but all of the \"service\" specific stuff (MGS, OSS, MDS) would still live in the specific directory and have all of the service-specific stuff defined there?  That avoids lumping everything into target.c and makes it easier to create new services in the future.",
      "accounts_in_message": [],
      "_revision_number": 2
    },
